member.name: P:Com.Xceder.Messages.Spreader.ReloadOffset
member.summary: Reload is an order that lets you execute a total spread order quantity by splitting the spread order into smaller disclosed quantities. When a disclosed spread order quantity is filled, the next disclosed quantity order is submitted until the entire spread order quantity fills. You can use the this property tick enter the market at the same price or a set number of ticks from the previously disclosed spread order. 0 will submit the new spread order at the same price as the previous spread order. 1 will submit the spread order at a price 1 tick from the previous spread order away from the market. -1 will submit the spread order 1 tick from the previous spread order toward the market.

member.name: P:Com.Xceder.Messages.Spreader.ReloadQty
member.summary: Reload is an order that lets you execute a total spread order quantity by splitting the spread order into smaller disclosed quantities. When a disclosed spread order quantity is filled, the next disclosed quantity order is submitted until the entire spread order quantity fills. This property specifies the quantity for each child disclosed order.

member.summary: limit in ticks a quoting order is allowed to work away from the price level that matches the spread differential 0: the spread differential price level and the quoting order will always requote to the price that matches the spread differential.

member.name: P:Com.Xceder.Messages.Spreader.Types.Leg.IsShortLeg
member.summary: indicate whether this leg is a short leg

member.name: P:Com.Xceder.Messages.Spreader.Types.Leg.QtyRatio
member.summary: quantity of this leg in relation to the other spread legs The Spread Ratio field allows a value of zero for spreads that require a leg for spread calculation purposes only, and not for entering orders as a part of the spread. When a leg has a value of zero in the Spread Ratio field, no quoting orders or hedge orders will be submitted in that leg as a part of a spread, but a spread fill is generated. The current inside market price at the time of the quoting leg fill will be used for the leg fill price when creating the spread fill. Values entered in the Spread Ratio field do not affect the spread price.

member.name: P:Com.Xceder.Messages.Spreader.Types.Leg.PriceWeight
member.summary: the multipler in the spread price formula

member.name: P:Com.Xceder.Messages.Spreader.Types.Leg.HedgeTick
member.summary: Example: You buy one ES Dec-Mar calendar spread at 6.00 and the quote leg fills at 2134.00. Payup Ticks are set to "-2" for the hedge leg and the contract ticks in ".25" increments. Instead of entering a sell order in the hedge leg for 2128.00 to achieve the spread price, Autospreader adjusts the price 2 ticks away from the market and enters an order at 2128.50. Using this same example but with Payup Ticks set to positive "2", Autospreader adjusts the spread price 2 ticks into the market and enters a hedge order at 2127.50.

member.name: P:Com.Xceder.Messages.Spreader.Types.Leg.MinQtyLean
member.summary: minimum quantity required for quoting orders to lean against If you want to lean only against the inside market and not lean on multiple levels of depth you can set the qtyLeanDepth to 0 and the minQtyLean to 1.

member.name: P:Com.Xceder.Messages.Spreader.Types.Leg.QtyLeanDepth
member.summary: Example: If the quantity on the second leg of the spread is 10 and the trader assigns an qtyLeanDepth of 2, Spreader determines the price level at which 20 contracts of cumulative market quantity exists on the second leg and uses this to determine the price at which it quotes the first leg of the spread.

member.name: P:Com.Xceder.Messages.Spreader.Types.Leg.QueueHolderDepth
member.summary: number of outright leg orders placed at consecutive price levels away from the inside market in addition to the single quoted order for each leg. Note: Queue Holder is only available with two-legged spreads.

member.name: P:Com.Xceder.Messages.Spreader.Types.Leg.MaxQuotePriceMove
member.summary: maximum number of ticks a leg price can move in a single price update before pulling the order this defines an order move threshold in the quoting leg. Setting these properties can help prevent legging risks in volatile markets. minimum setting is 1

member.name: P:Com.Xceder.Messages.Spreader.Types.Leg.MaxHedgePriceMove
member.summary: maximum number of ticks a leg price can move in a single price update before pulling the order from the market this defines a price move threshold in the leaning (hedging) leg. Setting these properties can help prevent legging risks in volatile markets. minimum setting is 1

member.name: P:Com.Xceder.Messages.Spreader.Types.Leg.SlopLevel
member.summary: Lets you configure multiple levels of slop to determine when to reprice the quoted outright legs based upon movement in the market

member.name: P:Com.Xceder.Messages.Spreader.Types.Leg.InsideQuote
member.summary: reduces excessive quoting away from the inside market. legs only requote when they are a set number of ticks away from the inside market

member.name: P:Com.Xceder.Messages.Spreader.Types.Leg.HedgeTriggerFillQty
member.summary: whether should send a hedge order when the quoted order is more than specified qty filled This setting is intended to be used for spreads with quoting orders more than double the quantity of the hedge order Once the entire hedge order fills and there is a quoting order working in the market, the quoting order is now the unhedged leg of the spread and will not reprice. Example: You are quoting 11 contracts and hedging 1. With Hedge trigger is set at 6, a hedge order is sent when 6 of the 11 contracts fill. When not set (0), all 11 contracts need to fill before 1 lot hedge is sent.

member.name: T:Xceder.CircularBuffer`1
member.summary:
Circular buffer.
When writting to a full buffer: PushBack -> removes this[0] / Front() PushFront -> removes this[Size-1] / Back()
this implementation is inspired by http://www.boost.org/doc/libs/1_53_0/libs/circular_buffer/doc/circular_buffer.html because I liked their interface.

member.summary: The _end. Index after the last element in the buffer.

member.name: M:Xceder.CircularBuffer`1.#ctor(System.Int32,`0[])
member.summary: Initializes a new instance of the class.
member.param: Items to fill buffer with. Items length must be less than capacity. Sugestion: use Skip(x).Take(y).ToArray() to build this argument from any enumerable.

member.name: P:Xceder.CircularBuffer`1.Capacity
member.summary: Maximum capacity of the buffer. Elements pushed into the buffer after maximum capacity is reached (IsFull = true), will remove an element.

member.summary: Current buffer size (the number of elements that the buffer has).

member.name: M:Xceder.CircularBuffer`1.Front
member.summary: Element at the front of the buffer - this[0].
member.returns: The value of the element of type T at the front of the buffer.

member.name: M:Xceder.CircularBuffer`1.Back
member.summary: Element at the back of the buffer - this[Size - 1].
member.returns: The value of the element of type T at the back of the buffer.

member.name: M:Xceder.CircularBuffer`1.PushBack(`0)
member.summary:
Pushes a new element to the back of the buffer. Back()/this[Size-1] will now return this element.
When the buffer is full, the element at Front()/this[0] will be popped to allow for this new element to fit.
member.param: Item to push to the back of the buffer

member.name: M:Xceder.CircularBuffer`1.PushFront(`0)
member.summary:
Pushes a new element to the front of the buffer. Front()/this[0] will now return this element.
When the buffer is full, the element at Back()/this[Size-1] will be popped to allow for this new element to fit.
member.param: Item to push to the front of the buffer

member.name: M:Xceder.CircularBuffer`1.PopBack(System.Int32)
member.summary: Removes the element at the back of the buffer. Decreassing the Buffer size by 1.

member.name: M:Xceder.CircularBuffer`1.PopFront(System.Int32)
member.summary: Removes the element at the front of the buffer. Decreassing the Buffer size by 1.

member.name: M:Xceder.CircularBuffer`1.ToArray
member.summary: Copies the buffer contents to an array, acording to the logical contents of the buffer (i.e. independent of the internal order/contents)
